</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,418]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Specimens present sculptured cuticle with polygonal areas over the dorsal body surface and the external side of the legs. On each leg, a gibbosity is present over the double-claws, which have smooth lunules at their base. Mean body size among the 
<specimenCount box="[540,699,272,298]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="generic">
<number box="[540,569,272,298]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="79.0">79</number>
specimens
</specimenCount>
collected was 
<number box="[872,916,272,298]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="442.0">442</number>
μm (SD 
<number box="[1023,1055,272,298]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="97.0">97</number>
), range 
<number box="[1149,1274,272,298]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="533.5" valueMax="770.0" valueMin="297.0">297 to 770</number>
μm. The species has been cited for Europe, Asia, 
<collectingCountry box="[599,700,312,338]" name="United States of America" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">America</collectingCountry>
and Africa. In the Iberian Peninsula, it has been recorded for 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,352,378]" name="Spain" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Spain</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="McInnes" box="[239,420,352,378]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29" refString="McInnes, S. J. (1994) Zoogeographic distribution of terrestrial / freshwater tardigrades from current literature. Journal of Natural History, 28, 257 - 352." type="journal article" year="1994">
McInnes 
<number box="[357,420,352,378]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first time it is recorded for Madrid (
<tableCitation box="[1054,1152,352,378]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,239,1706,1730]" captionTargetBox="[159,1400,1802,1996]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 2. Tardigrada species found in the Sierra de Guadarrama. New records (NR) for Europe (Eur), the Iberian Peninsula (IbPn), Spain (Spn) and Madrid Province (Mad) are indicated." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF5C665F3D5AFF91FF689BECFC06F97C" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" tableUuid="DF5C665F3D5AFF91FF689BECFC06F97C">
Table 
<number box="[1135,1152,352,378]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.0">2</number>
</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[1180,1436,352,377]" class="Eutardigrada" family="Hypsibiidae" genus="Doryphoribius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Parachela" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="flavus">
<emphasis box="[1180,1436,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Doryphoribius flavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appeared in 
<number box="[294,323,392,418]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="19.0">19</number>
of the sites sampled (Table 
<number box="[651,666,392,418]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="3.0">3</number>
) always in LF samples.
</paragraph>
